Thanh Le won this fight via Heel Hook🦶🔒Earlier in the week I saw the legendary BJJ Black Belt and UFC veteran Ryan Hall rolling and teaching Mikey Musumeci some techniques. Ryan is Le’s BJJ coach and a fighter who used Jiu-Jitsu Heel Hooks and leg locks so effectively that, in the UFC, people started to dodge him and not accept matches against him. I bring this up because for the non grappling fans Ryan Hall used this position from the ground called 50/50 which is like a leg triangle around your opponents thigh. Le used this 50/50 guard and played with off balancing his opponents footing until he fully secured the submission. But there was a key that was brilliant, at one point Ilya was leaning forward and had the opportunity to ground and pound but Le tightened his legs and held his palms forward to negate strikes, then bridged to sweep Illy down and then sunk in the submission. It was really high level grappling and an honor to have filmed this highlight at the event. Le was down to earth during interviews and even cracked jokes. Respect to you and your team, you guys are gems💎 @thanhlemma @ryanhall5050 #bjj #jiujitsu #grappling
